<tr>
<td class="article-body"><P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:date w:st="on" Year="2006" Day="15" Month="8"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>
<TABLE cellSpacing=2 cellPadding=2 border=0>
<TBODY>
<TR>
<TD>
<P align=center><A onclick="window.open('/Admin/spaw/img_popup.php?img_url=/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/AlexMinukMarat_1.jpg','Image','width=500,height=300,scrollbars=no,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,resizable=yes,screenX=120,screenY=100');return false;" href="#"><IMG height=140 src="/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/AlexMinukMaratsm.jpg" width=100 border=0></A><BR>Alex with Marat and his signed racquet</P></TD>
<TD>
<P align=center><A onclick="window.open('/Admin/spaw/img_popup.php?img_url=/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/IMG_752.jpg','Image','width=500,height=300,scrollbars=no,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,resizable=yes,screenX=120,screenY=100');return false;" href="#"><IMG height=133 src="/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/IMG_752sm.jpg" width=100 border=0></A><BR>Alex Minuk with his ticket</P></TD>
<TD>
<P align=center><A onclick="window.open('/Admin/spaw/img_popup.php?img_url=/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/Amitwithalex.jpg','Image','width=500,height=300,scrollbars=no,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,resizable=yes,screenX=120,screenY=100');return false;" href="#"><IMG height=154 src="/Admin/spaw/DatabaseImages/Amitwithalexsm.jpg" width=140 border=0></A><BR>Alex with Amit</P></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD colSpan=3>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><st1:date w:st="on" Year="2006" Day="15" Month="8"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>August 15, 2006</FONT></st1:date></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Hello Marat and Team</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Alex and I (Dad) would like to let you and your fans know of the experience we had when we were taken care of at the Rogers Cup by Marat’s team.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Firstly Alex is an avid young tennis player in <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:City w:st="on">Winnipeg</st1:City>, <st1:country-region w:st="on">Canada</st1:country-region></st1:place> who plays tennis about 5-6 days a week and is on the provincial tennis team. One of Alex’s favorite tennis players is Marat Safin. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Alex first made contact with “Webby” from the </FONT><A href="/"><U><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#800080 size=3>www.maratsafin.com</FONT></U></A><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3> web site and asked Marat if he would like to attend his Bar Mitzvah (a ceremony in the Jewish religion when a child becomes a man age 13) <st1:date w:st="on" Year="2006" Day="9" Month="9">September 9, 2006</st1:date>. As all good tennis fans know the summer is a very busy time for players like Marat and he said he was not able to come to Alex’s Bar Mitzvah but would send Alex a personal letter to commemorate his Bar Mitzvah. We were quite excited about the response by Webby and were hoping that a letter from Marat would not only be cherished by Alex but would also motivate him to keep working hard at tennis.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>About 2 months later Webby wrote to me and said that after a trip to Tel Aviv, Marat had changed his mind and felt that a letter was not recognition enough. He would instead like to send Alex an autographed racquet and a welcome for Alex and I to see Marat’s first round match at the Rogers Cup in <st1:City w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Toronto</st1:place></st1:City>. We were stunned by Marat’s generosity. The opportunity to go to the Rogers Cup had only been a dream to Alex and not a consideration of mine.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We were overwhelmed by the offer. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Our home is about 2100 km from <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:City w:st="on">Toronto</st1:City></st1:place>, so plane tickets would need to be found along with a place to stay. My brother lives about 70 km from <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:City w:st="on">Toronto</st1:City></st1:place> so we could stay with him and drive in every day. We arranged plane tickets, and emailed Webby that we were able to get tickets and had a place to stay while in <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:City w:st="on">Toronto</st1:City></st1:place>.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>We arranged to be at Rogers Cup Saturday to Wednesday (the tournament started with the preliminary matches Saturday and the first round started Monday). Webby said that she would arrange that the tournament secretary would have tickets for us for the days we there. Once there Amit (Marat’s friend/agent) would call us so that we could get in touch with Marat. So we were set.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Alex and I arrived in <st1:City w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Toronto</st1:place></st1:City> Saturday morning, got a car and went straight to the Rexall centre. We went to the Ticket booth and without any hitch picked up our complimentary tickets for Sunday to Wednesday. We explored the grounds and watched preliminary matches and players practice, like Nadal. On Sunday Alex got autographs and his picture taken with players like Seppi, Chela, Grosjean and Hernych. We had a great day and were also able to watch Federer practice.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Alex and I were very excited as it looked like we were going to meet Marat and Amit Monday. Around <st1:time w:st="on" Hour="13" Minute="0">1:00</st1:time> Marat was practicing at one of the separate practice courts which had a large area for fans to watch. Alex snuck in at the railing and had a great view of Marat, we took pictures and watched. We were feet from the court with the very large crowd watching. I made contact with Amit while he was on court and he told us he would speak to us after Marat finished practicing.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>After practice we met Amit who was very receptive to us. He welcomed us and as can be seen by the picture was exceptionally kind to Alex, hugging him and hoisting him up for a picture. Amit told Alex that he had one of Marat’s racquets with him and that Marat wanted to present it to him tomorrow. We were both so excited.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Tuesday we had a call from Amit that Marat was practicing at center court and that we could meet with Marat after he finished. We watched Marat practice and then after practice were called through the large crowd to meet with Marat. Marat gave Alex his Bar Mitzvah present (racquet) and signed a few tennis cards for him. I thanked Marat for all he had done for us, shook his hand and then we had run out of time, because the next match was going to start so we all had to leave. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Afterwards Alex was stunned, he could hardly speak. We checked over the pictures I had taken and they looked great. Alex’s smile was from ear to ear. Alex examined his Bar Mitzvah gift and was in awe.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Later Amit provided Alex and me with premium seats for Marat’s first round match against Robredo. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>So there we were center court in <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:City w:st="on">Toronto</st1:City></st1:place> in box seats with Marat Safin’s friend. Were we dreaming? The idea that Alex and me were sitting with Amit as Marat Safin’s guest was really a great feeling. We had felt so cared for by Marat’s organization it was remarkable. The privilege of being a Marat Safin fan was quite overwhelming, one we will never forget. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Unfortunately Marat lost to Robredo. The loss may have been hard for us to watch, but the performance by Marat for Alex was immeasurable.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He talks about his experience with all his tennis friends and has an original autographed Safin racket and pictures as a momento.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Now we are at home reflecting on our journey and experience. One can only think of the possibilities that may exist in life, when a young boy can message his favorite tennis star, <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>half way around the world and get to meet him. The fact is Safin wasn’t the only tennis star that Alex sent an email to, but the others never responded back at all. Safin it seems treats his fans at a level that so far exceeds the others, Safin’s fans are in a class by themselves. Marat Safin’s unexpected kindness and seemingly effortless consideration for his fans is unbelievable and makes him not only a great star but a truly great individual.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Thanks again</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3>Alex and Darrell Minuk</FONT></P></TD></TR>
